        Reloaxa

        Vote score

        Not a lot to say about this week other than a few things:

        *Lost Frequencies & Belters Only are getting closer to number 1 & I have a feeling that next week both are gonna challenge We Don't Talk About Bruno for the top.
        *Where Did You Go sits just outside the Top 10 & given how much I've grown to really like it, I'm not complaining.
        *With the release of his new mixtape (congrats on reaching Number 1) Central Cee's Retail Therapy was so close to re-entering the top 40 & it's a shame it hasn't as it's easily my favourite song he's done so far; good lyrics, nice rhyming scheme & an awesome beat. As for Khabib, which actually did re-enter... it's average. Lyrics are alright, but the weak link in the song for me is actually the beat. It isn't as catchy, nor does it hit as hard as Central Cee's other songs.
        *Do It To It has re-entered as well.
        *Closing in on the top 40 as well are Sigala's Melody & JNR Choi's To the Moon. Melody is musically fantastic with some great melodies & the lyrics are perfectly fine, but I don't like the vocals & the production isn't as good as a lot of Sigala's other songs. Still a decent song though. To the Moon however is one of the best produced & best sounding songs to hit the charts in a while. Makes up so much for the awful Auto-Tuned vocals (despite catchy flows) & lyrics, but I've had it on repeat non-stop regardless.
        *I didn't mention this last week but I'm BEYOND happy that Used to This by Wilkinson & Issey Cross broke the top 40. I already said my views on the song a few weeks ago & I'm very sure it'll be on my best list for 2022.
        *Sweet Talker & I Wish have gone on ACR. Neither are great, but they are both still solid enough dance tracks.

        Also, small side note - I hope for the love of God that Silenced by CamelPhat charts, because it's absolutely amazing & if you haven't heard it, you need to check it out. It's yet another 10/10 dance song I've heard in the past few months.

        New Entries:
        25. Central Cee - Straight Back to It (8/10)
        34. Becky Hill & Galantis - Run (7/10)
        54. Florence + the Machine - King (9/10) [Best of the Week]
        68. Tyga & Doja Cat - Freaky Deaky (6/10)
        71. Mura Masa - bbycakes (ft. Lil Uzi Vert, PinkPanthress & Shygirl) (2/10) [Worst of the Week]
        74. Labrinth & Zendaya - I'm Tired (5/10)
        94. Halsey - Could Have Been Me (4/10)
